PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779293476
OL,3,CChannel 4 boss 'deeply sorry' after
OL,4,CMarried At First Sight UK rape
OL,5,Callegations
OL,7,FIt also questioned the broadcaster
OL,8,Fabout its approach to the duty of care
OL,9,Fto participants on its other reality
OL,10,FTV programmes.
OL,12,FA CMS Committee message to Ofcom asks
OL,13,Fit about the role of the broadcasting
OL,14,Fregulator in the complaints process,
OL,15,Fits powers to investigate potential
OL,16,Fbreaches of the broadcasting code, and
OL,17,Fthe timeline for launching its own
OL,18,Finvestigation into the Married At
OL,19,FFirst Sight allegations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
